      "id": 348164,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "All aldoses exhibit mutarotation. For example, <i>α</i>-<small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small>-galactopyranose has [<i>α</i>]<sub><small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small></sub> = +150.7, and <i>β</i>-<small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small>-galactopyranose has [<i>α</i>]<sub><small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small></sub> = +52.8. If either anomer is dissolved in water and allowed to reach equilibrium, the specific rotation of the solution is +80.2. What are the percentages of each anomer at equilibrium? Draw the pyranose forms of both anomers.",
